sidebyside.p:
To eliminate the x-terms, we multiply the first equation by -2 and add:
            \begin{aligned}
                -2x+4y \amp = -6 \\
               \underline{2x-4y}\amp \underline{{}= \hphantom{-}6\vphantom{y}} \\
                0x+0y \amp = 0      
            \end{aligned}

